node.text:
SINCE WE WERE KIDS!

We grew up in the same neighborhood, listening to the same records, and we have been playing in this band together since 1981. Eli joined us upon his birth in 1985. Now we’re back with our first shows in a few years! Our 2021 Summer Tour kicks off this Sunday in Cumming, Iowa. We’ll see you there! FUCK YEAH!

node.text:
GROW YOUNG AGAIN

The sand ran out on yesterday; it was over. Everything I knew and had done since I was sixteen came to an abrupt end. But instead of growing up in that moment, I grew young again. And with the same Intensity, Passion, and Creativity I put into my Skating when I was a teenager, I put into my Skateboard Company, @streetplant, when I was forty-five. 

With the Love and Support of my Family, I started writing a new story—one without the impersonal demands of sponsors. Still, I continued to work with @triple8nyc to promote helmet use in Skateboarding. Not because they paid me to wear a helmet, but because I chose to wear a helmet, and they Supported me in that choice. Being free of other sponsors allowed me to put the helmet on and keep it on. And the good folks at @socco78 stuck it out with me as well, with no pressure at all. And six years went by in the blink of an eye.

Then @cariumaskateboarding called. A call I never expected and had given up on thinking was a possibility ever again. I genuinely thought that time in my Skateboard Life was over, and I was at peace with it. But what I've learned is that when you stop pursuing, things ensue and happen in their own time. And now, to be representing @cariuma, a company I revere for their Principles and Values, and to be on a team with the very best up and coming young Skaters in the world is Soul-Satisfying. And then to also have a Signature Shoe in development with such a Forward-Thinking company making the very best Skate Shoes—what more can I say? I'm Beyond Stoked. And at fifty-one, I can Appreciate this season more so than any other time in my Skateboard Life. 

All this to say THANK YOU to Cariuma, Triple 8, Socco, and @violentgentlemen for Believing in me and Supporting me in my Skating and my other endeavors. I count my Blessings daily. Much Love!

Photo: @jordon_vanzante

I spent my birthday adding hops to the boil on Brew Day for @streetplant Beer at @carrollbrewing in Carroll, IA. Street Plant is an American-style wheat that is hop forward with notes of citrus. Very Refreshing and Crushable! 4.7% ABV, and 19 IBUs. Coming Very Soon! Stay Tuned!

node.text:
My Family and I moved to Iowa six months ago, and we couldn’t be happier about our decision to put roots down here. We Love Des Moines, its people, Independent businesses, restaurants, coffee shops, breweries, and its Bike, Art, and emerging Skate culture. We have ridden our bikes hundreds and hundreds of miles and have enjoyed supporting the local sports teams: @iowawild, @bucshockey, and @iowacubs. We have ventured out to a different small-town, State Park, Wildlife Refuge, or Conservation Area almost every weekend that we have lived here. We do dearly miss our eldest daughter Emily, who stayed in California to pursue her dreams, and that’s been the only difficult part of the move for us. Big Love and Thanks to @subsect, @ichibike, @captroys, @dsmmercantile, and @slowdowndsm for being so welcoming to us; we Truly Appreciate it!

Video: @brent_roske for @dsmpartnership

node.text:
Bob Probert x @streetplant Tribute Boards

Available now at streetplant.com

It’s an honor to work with the Probert Family to produce these Bob Probert Tribute Boards. Bob is my All-Time favorite NHL player. In the early 90’s I wore a Detroit Red Wings hat that I had the number 24 embroidered on the back of — it was my good luck hat, and I was a Los Angeles Kings season ticket holder, haha.

No other player in the history of professional hockey had the presence on the ice or embodied the role of the tough guy like Bob Probert. When he was selected to play in the 1987-88 NHL All-Star Game, Wayne Gretzky and Mark Messier asked fellow superstar Steve Yzerman to introduce them to the “big fella.” Revered by teammates, opponents, and fans alike, there was never a player quite like him, and there never will be again. Bob was and is the All-Time Undisputed Heavyweight Champion of Professional Hockey.

Bob Probert Career Stats:

Games Played: 935
Goals: 163
Assists: 221
Points: 384
Penalty Minutes: 3,300
